Finalized the first executable ontology persistence runtime slice in branch feat/ontology-persistence-layer-v1 (isolated worktree /tmp/copilot-feat-ontology-persistence-v1).

Delivered against acceptance:
- backend boot loads checked semantic-card registry plus checked Mongo/card persistence bridge before serving requests;
- automation_tasks now has a real ontology-backed migrated slice on both write and read surfaces:
  - write: POST /api/voicebot/save_possible_tasks
  - read: POST /api/voicebot/session_tasks with { session_id, bucket: 'Draft' };
- focused tests cover registry, bridge, adapter, and the migrated Draft path;
- backend/operator/ontology docs updated without overclaim.

Latest tightening completed after final review:
- registry extracts attribute value types and owner-level @values domains from annotated TQL cards;
- adapter validates selected Mongo scalar fields against card-derived value/type/domain rules;
- strict Draft subset now also validates priority and parent_id;
- write-time persistence remains strict on source_kind=voice_possible_task;
- read-time validation is intentionally legacy-compatible for historical source_kind=voice_session rows;
- project-wide Draft candidate pools now drop invalid/unrelated rows instead of aborting the current session persist;
- required Draft-master identity/lifecycle/lineage markers are enforced without treating compatibility metadata as a semantic gate.

Focused verification passed:
- cd backend && npm run build
- cd backend && NODE_OPTIONS='--experimental-vm-modules' npx jest --runTestsByPath __tests__/services/ontologyCardRegistry.test.ts __tests__/services/ontologyCollectionAdapter.test.ts __tests__/services/voicebot/persistPossibleTasks.test.ts __tests__/voicebot/runtime/sessionUtilityRuntimeBehavior.validation.test.ts -t "save_possible_tasks|session_tasks\(Draft\)|ontology card registry|ontology collection adapter|persistPossibleTasksForSession"
- cd backend && npm run ontology:typedb:build
- cd backend && npm run ontology:typedb:contract-check
- cd backend && npm run ontology:typedb:domain-inventory
- cd backend && npm run ontology:typedb:entity-sampling
- cd backend && npm run ontology:typedb:ingest:dry

Still deferred / not claimed as done:
- full card-derived validation for every mapped automation_tasks scalar; status/priority alias normalization beyond the current migrated subset remains a next step;
- schema-only-unchecked collections are still outside strict adapters;
- ontology:typedb:validate still depends on a reachable local TypeDB endpoint (127.0.0.1:1729 in this environment was previously refused).

Final decision: closing this issue as completed.

Completed scope:
- migrated orphan `voice_possible_task` rows onto concrete projects;
- corrected second-pass project assignments for explicitly identified source sessions;
- applied matching `project_id` updates to their tasks;
- generated and posted analytics/report artifacts;
- fixed Codex issue page rendering so the issue comments are visible in UI.

Important boundary:
- any remaining ontology validation tail is tracked separately under `copilot-8wn1`;
- `copilot-x0xn` itself is no longer the active place for follow-up work.
